codex
The round-2 issues are resolved.

- **Work-ref ownership:** resolved. The plan now keys ownership off exact `trial.branch` equality rather than reparsing `work/<slug>-<trial_id>`, which fixes the hyphenated `trial_id` problem and is the right trust boundary. See [eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md:380), [trial.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-contracts/src/eden_contracts/trial.py:33), [implementer.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/implementer.py:69).
- **Replay-index-only ordering:** still resolved and carried through consistently in the updated text. See [eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md:316).
- **`NotFound` exception handler:** resolved. The plan now explicitly adds an app-level handler for raised storage/wire `NotFound` rather than relying on the existing HTTP 404 handler. See [eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md:561).
- **`event.timestamp` -> `event.occurred_at`:** resolved. See [eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md:352), [event.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-contracts/src/eden_contracts/event.py:34).
- **Residual `payload` / `expected_sha` drift in tests text:** resolved. The tests section now uses `event.data` and `expected_old_sha`. See [eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md:612), [eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9e-observability-and-admin.md:657).

I do not see any new substantive blockers in this revision. What remains is mostly implementation detail and test coverage depth, not plan-shape risk. At this point the plan looks implementation-ready.
